{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778377908164,"sessionID":"ses_1f06cb1ecffe4eQwWh340yWv8Y","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"bash","callID":"call_sF7AxFASUkZdYTJZw1IqzPZU","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"command":"git diff -- 'src/ontology/uberon-edit.obo'","timeout":120000,"workdir":"/__w/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon","description":"Shows ontology edit diff"},"output":"diff --git a/src/ontology/uberon-edit.obo b/src/ontology/uberon-edit.obo\nindex 36afa06..798c73b 100644\n--- a/src/ontology/uberon-edit.obo\n+++ b/src/ontology/uberon-edit.obo\n@@ -9020,15 +9020,15 @@ consider: WBbt:0005441\n \n [Term]\n id: UBERON:0000961\n-name: thoracic ganglion\n-def: \"The thoracic ganglia are paravertebral ganglia. The thoracic portion of the sympathetic trunk typically has 12 thoracic ganglia. Emerging from the ganglia are thoracic splancic nerves (the cardiopulmonary, the greater, lesser, and least splanchic nerves) that help provide sympathetic innervation to abdominal structures. Also, the ganglia of the thoracic sympathetic trunk have both white and gray rami communicantes. The white rami carry sympathetic fibers arising in the spinal cord into the sympathetic trunk. [WP,unvetted].\" [Wikipedia:Thoracic_ganglion]\n+name: thoracic paravertebral ganglion\n+def: \"A paravertebral ganglion that is part of the thoracic sympathetic nerve trunk. The thoracic portion of the sympathetic trunk typically has 12 thoracic paravertebral ganglia. Emerging from the ganglia are thoracic splanchnic nerves (the cardiopulmonary, the greater, lesser, and least splanchnic nerves) that help provide sympathetic innervation to abdominal structures. Also, the ganglia of the thoracic sympathetic trunk have both white and gray rami communicantes. The white rami carry sympathetic fibers arising in the spinal cord into the sympathetic trunk. [WP,unvetted].\" [Wikipedia:Thoracic_ganglion]\n subset: uberon_slim\n-synonym: \"ganglion of thorax\" EXACT [OBOL:automatic]\n+synonym: \"gangli